<TITLE> DSE turnover tops Tk 6 bn to touch new high </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 11 (bdnews24.com)Turnover on the Dhaka Stock Exchange hit a new record Thursday, crossing the Tk 6 billion mark. The country's prime bourse saw Tk 6.11 billion changing hands through trading of 37,541,462 shares, up from Wednesday's turnover of Tk 5.88 billion. The previous high was Tk 5.90 billion in October last year. Turnover on the Chittagong Stock Exchange also surged to Tk 703.139 million from Tk 626.233 million on Wednesday, with 6,256,994 shares traded. Market observers said investors are betting more on shares anticipating a vibrant market in the near future. "Different levels of investors are putting money in seeing the last few days' upbeat trend that pumped up turnover and trading volume," economist Abu Ahmed told bdnews24.com. "The reason behind the hype is companies are now declaring dividends," added Ahmed, an adviser to the Securities and Exchange Commission. The DSE opened up, though profit-taking caused losses in the midday session. The DGEN or general index edged down 1.86 points or 0.07 percent to finish at 2653.11. The DSI or all share price index ended on 2206.18, shedding 1.53 points or 0.06 percent. The bourse's blue-chip DSE-20 rose 3.33 points or 0.15 percent to 2144.53. Of the traded issues, 131 gained, 120 lost and eight remained unchanged. Indices on the Chittagong Stock Exchange ended upbeat paced by gains in engineering, ceramic and textile shares. The CSCX or selective categories index gained 24.52 points or 0.46 percent to close at 5274.74. The CASPI or all share price index ended at 8172.71, rising 35.24 points or 0.43 percent. The CSE-30 blue-chip index rose 39.59 points or 0.61 percent to 6517.76. Of the traded issues, 95 advanced and 81 declined with three scrips holding steady. Top ten by turnover on DSE Shinepukur Ceramics shrugged off losses, ending 6.10 percent up on Tk 113. S Alam Cold Rolled Steels surged 17.74 percent to Tk 579. Power sector heavyweight Summit Power eroded the previous day's gains, closing 3.75 percent down at Tk 998.50. Beximco Pharmaceuticals was up again following Wednesday's losses; it rose 2.93 percent to close at Tk 165.10. Beximco closed at Tk 193.50, rising 7.20 percent. Among the other scrips on the turnover boardBSRSM Steel, Eastern Housing Ltd, Golden Sons Ltd and Quasem Dry Cells also ended up. Profit-taking led Summit Alliance Port Ltd to lose.
